@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    BnDemo — Phase 3.4 Task 4 (design §4): the Bn*-built demo form closing
    M3 DoD #5 (two-way bound input + live echo) and DoD #6 (cascading theme
    toggle → themed children re-render). Phase 3.5 (design §2) makes it a
    TWO-PAGE app: the "Settings →" button navigates to BnSettingsPage
    (route "/settings") through [Inject] INavigationManager — DoD #7.
    Registered as "BnDemo" in HostSession's mount registry; MainActivity's
    default since 3.4 Gate 4.

    Phase 7.1 Gate 2: authored in .razor (the HARD conversion — @bind-Value
    on a component, cascading BnTheme, four event handlers, BnThemedPanel →
    BnView chaining, the live echo). Parity with the retired hand-written
    BuildRenderTree version was proven byte-for-byte by the transitional
    golden-vs-twin test — record-identical patch streams across mount +
    bind/echo + Clear + the theme flip both ways + the Settings navigation,
    mutation-verified — before the swap; BnDemoTests + NavigationTests +
    both shells' suites hold it from here.

    @bind-Value="_text" on BnInput is the compiler's component-pair
    inference (spike conclusion, implication 3): Value/ValueChanged are
    inferred from the component's parameters — no element bind metadata,
    nothing new shipped. It expands to exactly the pair the retired page
    wired by hand: Value=_text + ValueChanged=(__value => _text = __value).

    Shape (the pinned mount contract — BnDemoTests + Gate 3's BnDemoTest.kt):
      CascadingValue<BnTheme>                       (region — no node)
      └─ BnScroll (#204)                             scroll — flexGrow 1, flexBasis 0
         │                                           the shells interpose a SYNTHETIC
         │                                           content node under it; the form
         │                                           parents into THAT, never into the
         │                                           viewport (6.2 non-negotiable #2)
         └─ BnThemedPanel #1 → BnView form div       backgroundColor+padding 16
            ├─ BnText  title "BnDemo"                span, fontSize 24
            ├─ BnInput bound (@bind-Value)           input: value+placeholder+change
            ├─ BnThemedPanel #2 → BnView echo panel  div, backgroundColor+padding 8
            │   └─ BnText echo (= the bound text)    span
            ├─ BnButton "Clear"                      button + click
            ├─ BnButton "Theme"                      button + click
            └─ BnButton "Settings →"                 button + click → NavigateToAsync("/settings")
      (4 event attaches: change + Clear + Theme + Settings →)

    The bind loop (DoD #5): change dispatch → BnInput.ValueChanged → _text
    mutates → re-render → echo ReplaceText + input value UpdateProp.
    The theme toggle (DoD #6): _theme swaps to a NEW BnTheme record →
    CascadingValue notifies → BOTH BnThemedPanels re-render → SetStyle
    backgroundColor on both divs.
    The navigation (DoD #7): Settings click → INavigationManager swaps the
    root (this page's RemoveNodes, then BnSettingsPage's creates) inside the
    same dispatch.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
@* Grow="1" Basis="0" — CSS's `flex: 1`, and BOTH halves are load-bearing.
   Grow alone leaves flexBasis at `auto`, so the viewport's basis is its own
   CONTENT's height; against a shorter host the free space is NEGATIVE, flexGrow
   never distributes negative space, and the shrink pass does nothing because
   Yoga defaults flexShrink to 0. The viewport would keep its content's height,
   equal its own content, and scroll nothing — the exact silent failure
   BnScroll's KDoc documents and WidgetMapperScrollTest pins. Basis="0" is what
   makes the free space positive again.

   The host root IS a bounded parent (widget_root is the whole Activity since
   #204), which is the other half of the requirement.

   No Padding/Gap/Direction here: those are absent from BnScroll BY CONSTRUCTION
   — they would land on the viewport, whose only Yoga child is the synthetic
   content node, and fail silently. The BnThemedPanel inside keeps its own
   Padding="16", which is exactly the composition the component's docs
   prescribe. *@
<CascadingValue Value="_theme">
    <BnScroll Grow="1" Basis="0">
        <BnThemedPanel Padding="16">
            <BnText Text="BnDemo" FontSize="24" />
            <BnInput @bind-Value="_text" Placeholder="Type here..." />
            <BnThemedPanel Padding="8">
                <BnText Text="@_text" />
            </BnThemedPanel>
            <BnButton Label="Clear" OnClick="Clear" />
            <BnButton Label="Theme" OnClick="ToggleTheme" />
            <BnButton Label="Settings →" OnClick="GoToSettings" />
        </BnThemedPanel>
    </BnScroll>
</CascadingValue>

@code {
    private const string DefaultBackground = "#FFEEAA";
    private const string AltBackground = "#334455";

    private string _text = "";
    private BnTheme _theme = new(DefaultBackground, AltBackground);

    /// <summary>Phase 3.5: the navigation service (Core contract) — same
    /// explicit [Inject] public property as the hand-written page (NOT
    /// @inject, which generates a private property).</summary>
    [Inject] public INavigationManager Navigation { get; set; } = default!;

    private void Clear() => _text = "";

    // Swap: a NEW record instance each toggle (see BnTheme doc).
    private void ToggleTheme()
        => _theme = new BnTheme(_theme.AltBackground, _theme.Background);

    // Sync-completing (inline dispatcher): the swap has fully happened —
    // removes + creates delivered — when this Task is observed.
    private Task GoToSettings() => Navigation.NavigateToAsync("/settings").AsTask();
}
